Description: fix 64-bit portability issues
 Replace long with Uint32 for all time values (Timer::getTime, Timer::delay,
 xdm time variables, all scene/gfx draw() signatures). On LP64 (Linux 64-bit),
 long is 64 bits but time values are milliseconds that fit in Uint32, making
 long unnecessarily wide and inconsistent with SDL types.
 .
 Fix signed/unsigned comparison: replace (unsigned)++current_scene+1 > size()
 with (size_t)++current_scene >= size() for correct semantics on LP64.
 .
 Fix implicit narrowing: scene[scene.size()] uses size_t as int map key;
 explicit cast added.
 .
 Fix undefined behaviour in loadPNG: row_pointers was allocated with malloc()
 but freed with delete[]. Replaced with proper free() for each row and the
 pointer array. Also frees the individual rows that were previously leaked.
 .
 Fix undefined behaviour in pixel construction: (int)(ptr[0]<<16) shifts a
 promoted-to-int u8 value which may overflow into the sign bit if the byte
 value has bit 7 set (e.g. ptr[0]=255 gives 0xFF000000 as int = UB).
 Cast to u32 before shifting.
 .
 Fix pixel index arithmetic in getPixel/setPixel and loadPNG: x + y*w computed
 as int can theoretically overflow for large surfaces. Use size_t indexing.
 .
 Replace unsigned int loop variable with size_t when iterating over
 std::string::length() in loadOne.
